<p>
<strong>TABLE OF CONTENTS FOR THE SOUTH CAROLINA VOLUME</strong>
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh4.htm">CHAPTER I.</a> Spirit of Secession--The State Militia
--Charleston and the Forts--The Violated Agreement--
Major Anderson Occupies Fort Sumter--South Carolina Occupies Pinckney
and Moultrie--The Star of the West--Fort Sumter Surrendered--Carolinians
in Virginia--Battle of Manassas
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh29.htm">CHAPTER II.</a> Affairs on the Coast--Loss of Port
 Royal Harbor--Gen. R. E. Lee in Command of the Department-Landing of
 Federals at Port Royal Ferry--Gallant Fight on Edisto Island--
General Pemberton Succeeds Lee in Command--Defensive Line, April, 1862
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh43.htm">CHAPTER III.</a> South Carolinians in Virginia
--Battle of Williamsburg--Eltham's Landing--Seven Pines
 and Fair Oaks--Nine-Mile Road--Gaines' Mill--Savage Station
--Frayser's Farm--Malvern Hill
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh76.htm">CHAPTER IV.</a> The Coast of South Carolina,
 Summer of 1862--Operations under General Pemberton--Engagement at
 Old Pocotaligo---Campaign on James Island--Battle of Secessionville
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh94.htm">CHAPTER V.</a> General Beauregard in Command
--The Defenses of Charleston -- Disposition of Troops-- Battle of
 Pocotaligo---Repulse of Enemy at Coosawhatchie Bridge
--Operations in North Carolina--Battle of Kinston
--Defense of Goldsboro
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh111.htm">CHAPTER VI.</a> South Carolinians in the West
--Manigault's and Lythgoe's Regiments at Corinth
--The Kentucky Campaign--Battle of Murfreesboro
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh120.htm">CHAPTER VII.</a> With Lee in Northern Virginia, 1862
--The Maneuvers on the Rappahannock--Second Manassas Campaign
--Battle of Ox Hill.
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh140.htm">CHAPTER VIII.</a> The Maryland Campaign
--The South Mountain Battles--Capture of Harper's Ferry
--Battles of Sharpsburg and Shepherdstown
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh165.htm">CHAPTER IX.</a> Hampton's Cavalry in the Maryland
 Raid-The Battle of Fredericksburg--Death of Gregg
--South Carolinians at Marye's Hill--Cavalry Operations
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh188.htm">CHAPTER X. </a> Operations in South Carolina,
Spring of 1863-Capture of the Isaac Smith
--Ingraham s Defeat of the Blockading Squadron
--Naval Attack on Fort Sumter-Hunter's Raids
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh203.htm">CHAPTER XI.</a> South Carolina Troops in
 Mississippi--Engagement near Jackson--The Vicksburg Campaign
--Siege of Jackson
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh213.htm">CHAPTER XII.</a> South Carolinians in the
 Chancellorsville Campaign-- Service of Kershaw's and McGowan's Brigades
--A Great Confederate Victory
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh223.htm">CHAPTER XIII.</a> Operations in South Carolina
--Opening of Gillmore's Campaign against Fort Sumter
--The Surprise of Morris Island--First Assault on Battery Wagner
--Demonstrations on James Island and Against the Railroad
--Action near Grimball's Landing
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh235.htm">CHAPTER XIV.</a> Second Assault on Battery Wagner
--Siege of Wagner and Bombardment of Fort Sumter
--Evacuation of Morris Island
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh257.htm">CHAPTER XV.</a> The Gettysburg Campaign
--Gallant Service of Perrin's and Kershaw's Brigades
--Hampton's Cavalry at Brandy Station
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh277.htm">CHAPTER XVI.</a> South Carolinians at Chickamauga
--Organization of the Armies--- South Carolinians Engaged
--Their Heroic Service and Sacrifices
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh291.htm">CHAPTER XVII.</a> The Siege of Charleston
--Continued Bombardment of Fort Sumter
--Defense Maintained by the Other Works
--The Torpedo Boats--Bombardment of the City--
Transfer of Troops to Virginia--Prisoners under Fire
--Campaign on the Stono
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh310.htm">CHAPTER XVIII.</a> South Carolinians with 
Longstreet and Lee--Wauhatchie--Missionary Ridge--Knoxville
--The Virginia Campaign of 1864
--From the Wilderness to the Battle of the Crater
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh328.htm">CHAPTER XIX.</a> The Atlanta Campaign
--Battles around Atlanta--Jonesboro
--Hood's Campaign in North Georgia
--The Defense of Ship's Gap--Last Campaign in Tennessee
--Battle of Franklin
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh346.htm">CHAPTER XX.</a> The Closing Scenes in Virginia
-- Siege of Richmond and Petersburg--Fall of Fort Fisher
--South Carolina Commands at Appomattox
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh354.htm">CHAPTER XXI.</a> Battle of Honey Hill
--Sherman's Advance into South Carolina
--Organization of the Confederate Forces
--Burning of Columbia--Battles of Averasboro and Bentonville
--- Conclusion
<p>
<li><!a href="cmh373.htm">BIOGRAPHICAL</a>
